    "description": "<p>Simple in make and function, these prostheses aren&rsquo;t fancy, but they get the job done. These might include simplistic wooden hands or peg prostheses, or slightly more refined&nbsp;designs where gravity is used to maneuver the joints.</p>\n<p>Effect: While wearing a Basic Prosthesis, the limb has a full range of mobility and function, and any reduction to SPD is negated. Due to its lack of fine motor function, all attack and defense checks made with a prosthetic arm are made at a -3. In the case of a Basic Prosthetic Leg, all Dodge/Escape checks are made at a -1.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Additionally, a Basic Prosthesis cannot be used to channel Chaos. Any attack made against a prosthetic limb is redirected towards its wearer for gameplay purposes.</p>",
